          <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-12 mb-6">Considering Maharashtra and Gujarat for example, Different Conditions, Same Underlying Risk</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">In Maharashtra, the Mumbai-Pune-Nashik-Aurangabad belt runs real estate, metro, and industrial shed construction straight through a June-to-September monsoon that doesn't let up. MIDC industrial zones keep fabrication and assembly work going on platforms that are wet for most of that window, and the volume of active sites means the risk isn't isolated to one project type. It's a feature of the season across the region.</p>
          <p class="text-slate-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Gujarat carries a different version of the same problem. The Ahmedabad-Vadodara-Surat-Rajkot corridor and its GIDC zones run heavy EPC, petrochemical, and textile construction activity year-round, and the coastal and chemical-belt humidity around areas like Dahej and Hazira adds a corrosion load that inland sites in Maharashtra don't see in the same way. A painted plank degrades faster there. A galvanized one earns its cost back faster too.</p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-12 mb-6">Before the Rains Peak, Not After an Incident</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Check your current decking now, while you still have the option to swap it out on your own schedule instead of reacting to a near-miss or a failed inspection. Prime Steeltech manufactures anti-skid walkway planks, with galvanized options for sites that need the corrosion resistance, and hook-on ends built to connect fast and securely to Cuplock and Ringlock systems when a platform needs re-securing after rain.</p>
          
          <p class="font-bold text-lg text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-10">
            If you're specifying decking for the season ahead, <a href="/quote" class="text-emerald-600 hover:text-emerald-700 underline underline-offset-4 decoration-emerald-300">request a quote or a technical spec sheet</a> and we'll work out what fits your spans and load conditions.
